SELF-PROCLAIMED prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, Mary, are expected to make an appearance at the Pretoria Magistrates Court this morning for the continuation of their bail application. The couple made their first appearance on Wednesday after their arrest by the Hawks on Tuesday. They are facing charges of fraud and money laundering amounting to R102 million along with the other three accused. The state is expected to respond to the Bushiris’ application. Prophet Bushiri supporters chanted outside the Pretoria Magistrate Court on Friday to support their Prophet and his wife, Mary Bushiri. pic.twitter.com/zLDT1ShHSO   The state opposed their bail application, stating that they were not ready and they still need to investigate more details on the suspects.  Bushiri’s followers are expected to come in their numbers outside the court. 